						<b>Hapja-juk (rice gruel with mussels)</b><br><br>
						Cooked honghap (hard-shelled mussel) and crushed rice are stir-fried with sesame oil and then water is added to boil. It is seasoned with onion juice, garlic juice, and salts.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="10" border="0"></td></tr>
